{"$ambrosia":"aero:interactive:9417ac60-5f60-11ea-8e69-affb2224d7e8:*","$id":"f34710b0-44df-11ed-83e7-c45c2ac56969","$workspaceId":"7fff47c0-44d6-11ed-bcef-d5307f42495c","$projectId":"86cb0040-44df-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca","annotations":[],"configSchemaVersion":"/pluginGenericSchema/v1","config":{"stage":{"sections":[{"rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"4cad927e-d554-4c52-9d03-0aa82973ffbf","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Computing the Outstanding Loan Balance","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"242412a7-8d2a-416e-a082-d61daeade138"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"15127747-efb0-45c8-bb40-c02b42f2ff4f","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"As ","marks":[]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","ref":"981d3b62-cd26-4c95-9a5d-5b528b1ff1da","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Figure 5.1","marks":[]}],"data":{"reference":"fe328440-44e0-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"}},{"object":"text","text":" shows, the outstanding balance on an amortizing loan is different each month. The amount you owe at any point can be calculated as the present value of your future obligations on the loan. So, the outstanding balance, also called the ","marks":[]},{"object":"text","text":"outstanding principal","marks":[{"type":"italic"}]},{"object":"text","text":", is equal to the present value of the remaining future loan payments, again evaluated using the loan interest rate. We calculate the outstanding loan balance by determining the present value of the remaining loan payments using the loan rate as the discount rate.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"a4ecad4d-22ae-417c-a1d6-3e108f2a0ea6"}]}]}]},{"cssClass":"aside-group example_1","rows":[{"columns":[{"stageElements":[{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-two","ref":"9fa87def-765f-45fe-a0bf-c59e984a38d3","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Personal Finance: Example 5.3 Computing the Outstanding Loan Balance","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"adafeec0-c3a4-46b9-ad87-a1d64e7cde5e"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-three","ref":"b15dd38b-40b1-43e7-ba4d-04f95b958f45","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Problem","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"4b76848f-e896-4db1-bb83-372b6a33ffff"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"37fbd4b6-2ec8-4e76-be22-9acb425e51f4","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Let’s say that you are now three years into your $30,000 car loan from the previous section and you decide to sell the car. When you sell the car, you will need to pay whatever the remaining balance is on your car loan. After 36 months of payments, how much do you still owe on your car loan?","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"7f8ba180-0a3d-4741-b209-9a136685ec17"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-three","ref":"ff50e889-6d75-49aa-9e3e-d63e2bd91aa6","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Solution","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"f266f572-18b0-4f6b-92f8-c31b1ea09cd2"},{"type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"heading-four","ref":"12c4a714-d151-4f67-b00f-0b88fd15b8c1","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Plan","marks":[]}],"data":{}}]}},"config":{"cssClass":""},"ref":"639bbaeb-f1d9-477d-ac1e-f3e8b7142624"},{"type":"sta